For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND PROVISIONS OF THE ARKANSAS CODE TO
10 PROVIDE SCHOOL DISTRICTS WITH FLEXIBILITY REGARDING
11 ALTERNATIVE LEARNING ENVIRONMENTS; AND FOR OTHER
12 PURPOSES.
13
14
Subtitle
15
16 TO AMEND PROVISIONS OF THE ARKANSAS CODE
17 TO PROVIDE SCHOOL DISTRICTS WITH
18 FLEXIBILITY REGARDING ALTERNATIVE
19 LEARNING ENVIRONMENTS.
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
22
23 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 6-18-503(a)(1)(C), concerning disciplinary
24 policies required for public school districts, is amended to read as follows:
25 (C) The discipline policy required under subdivision
26 (a)(1)(A) of this section shall include provisions for:
27 (i) Placement of a student with disciplinary,
28 socially dysfunctional, or behavioral problems not associated with a physical
29 or mental impairment or disability in an alternative learning environment
30 provided by the district, if the district provides an alternative learning
31 environment; and
32 (ii) Procedures for responding to reports received
33 through the school safety and crisis line under § 6-18-111.
34
35 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 6-48-102 is amended to read as follows:
36 6-48-102. Alternative learning environment required — Reporting.
*TNL357*
03/19/2025 5:08:19 PM TNL357

HB1903
1 (a)(1) A school district shall may provide one (1) or more alternative
2 learning environments for all students who meet the minimum criteria
3 established by the Division of Elementary and Secondary Education.
4 (2) A school district complies with this section if the school
5 district provides may provide an alternative learning environment by one (1)
6 or more of the following methods:
7 (A) Establishes and operates Establishing and operating an
8 alternative learning environment;
9 (B) Cooperates Cooperating with one (1) or more other
10 school districts to establish and operate an alternative learning
11 environment;
12 (C) Uses Using an alternative learning environment
13 operated by an education service cooperative established under The Education
14 Service Cooperative Act of 1985, § 6-13-1001 et seq.; or
15 (D) Partners Partnering with a state-supported institution
16 of higher education and technical institutes to provide concurrent courses or
17 technical education options for academic learning to students in grades eight
18 through twelve (8-12).
19 (b) Annually, a school district that provides an alternative learning
20 environment under this section shall submit to the division:
21 (1) Information on race and gender of the students educated in
22 the alternative learning environment;
23 (2) Any other information regarding students educated in
24 alternative learning environments that the division requires by rule; and
25 (3) An assurance statement that the school district is in
26 compliance with this chapter.
